  "text": "Christmas is coming. For some, that means snow on the ground, but as areas get less snow than in previous years, that means more regular Christmases than White Christmases in the United States. For Bloomberg, Denise Lu mapped the last time cities had at least one inch of snow fall or accumulation. Compared to Christmases since 1970, last year’s holiday had the lowest average snow on the ground across the continental US. The chance for a white Christmas this year may be higher than last year, according to AccuWeather, but many areas will likely still not see any snow. Bonus points for the shoveler with a Santa hat that doubles as a progress bar: This is in contrast to the Washington Post piece from last week. WaPo used similar data from NOAA but highlighted cumulative snowfall instead of the lack of it.",
  "image": "https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu.png",
  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"single-post\"\u003e\n        \n                \n        \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"750\" height=\"420\" src=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-750x420.png\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-750x420.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-1090x610.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-210x118.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-768x430.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-1536x860.png 1536w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-2048x1146.png 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" data-attachment-id=\"76927\" data-permalink=\"https://flowingdata.com/2024/12/23/when-cities-last-saw-snow-on-christmas/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu/\" data-orig-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu.png\" data-orig-size=\"2432,1361\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-750x420.png\" data-large-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/snow-accumulation-bloomberg-lu-1090x610.png\"/\u003e                    \u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n                                    \n                \u003cp\u003eChristmas is coming. For some, that means snow on the ground, but as areas get less snow than in previous years, that means more regular Christmases than White Christmases in the United States. For Bloomberg, Denise Lu mapped the \u003ca href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/graphics/2024-christmas-snow-data/?accessToken=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzb3VyY2UiOiJTdWJzY3JpYmVyR2lmdGVkQXJ0aWNsZSIsImlhdCI6MTczNDk4MDQ3MiwiZXhwIjoxNzM1NTg1MjcyLCJhcnRpY2xlSWQiOiJTT1hZRzdEV1gyUFQwMCIsImJjb25uZWN0SWQiOiIzRDhGMEEzMTc2MDc0NUM5OTg4NkFCNzA1NDk2RUNEQSJ9.PQLXTBV0LilHAnYaupMlLAokSuG8tlkeR1qSF7Qi4VI\"\u003elast time cities had at least one inch of snow fall or accumulation\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\u003cp\u003eCompared to Christmases since 1970, last year’s holiday had the lowest average snow on the ground across the continental US. The chance for a white Christmas this year may be higher than last year, according to AccuWeather, but many areas will likely still not see any snow.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBonus points for the shoveler with a Santa hat that doubles as a progress bar:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"76928\" data-permalink=\"https://flowingdata.com/2024/12/23/when-cities-last-saw-snow-on-christmas/denise-lu-shovel-snow/\" data-orig-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow.png\" data-orig-size=\"1342,276\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"denise-lu-shovel-snow\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-750x154.png\" data-large-file=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-1090x224.png\" src=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-750x154.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"154\" srcset=\"https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-750x154.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-1090x224.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-210x43.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow-768x158.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/denise-lu-shovel-snow.png 1342w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is in contrast to the \u003ca href=\"https://flowingdata.com/2024/12/20/counting-the-christmas-days-with-snow/\"\u003eWashington Post piece\u003c/a\u003e from last week. WaPo used similar data from \u003ca href=\"https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/products/land-based-station/global-historical-climatology-network-daily?itid=lk_inline_enhanced-template\"\u003eNOAA\u003c/a\u003e but highlighted cumulative snowfall instead of the lack of it. \u003c/p\u003e\n                \n                \n                                        \n  